[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":348},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F":325,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F":334},"\u002Fdocker\u002F20220423\u002F196903828\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":308,"date":309,"description":310,"extension":311,"lang":312,"meta":313,"navigation":314,"path":315,"readingMinutes":316,"seo":317,"standalone":318,"stem":319,"tags":320,"tldr":322,"updated":309,"url":323,"__hash__":324},"content\u002Fen\u002FDocker\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix.md","Docker `denied: requested access to the resource is denied` — How to Fix","5098612556",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":298},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,36,113,120,124,127,146,151,158,164,167,184,190,198,201,205,211,220,238,243,249,253,259,265,271,277,281,294],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"I was trying to push to Docker Hub recently and kept hitting ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"denied: requested access to the resource is denied",". Here's a writeup of the fixes.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"the-problem","The problem",[17,30,31,32,35],{},"When I ran ",[21,33,34],{},"docker push localImageName",":",[37,38,43],"pre",{"className":39,"code":40,"language":41,"meta":42,"style":42},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","Using default tag: latest\nThe push refers to repository [docker.io\u002Flibrary\u002Ftest]\nd8deea6aacf6: Preparing \nd31b1b3688ec: Preparing \n859d050b8423: Preparing \n5f70bf18a086: Preparing \n9164c306cc0a: Preparing \n8396c878c66c: Waiting \n3ee39e78fd25: Waiting \n138331e9552c: Waiting \ndenied: requested access to the resource is denied\n","cmd","",[21,44,45,53,59,65,71,77,83,89,95,101,107],{"__ignoreMap":42},[46,47,50],"span",{"class":48,"line":49},"line",1,[46,51,52],{},"Using default tag: latest\n",[46,54,56],{"class":48,"line":55},2,[46,57,58],{},"The push refers to repository [docker.io\u002Flibrary\u002Ftest]\n",[46,60,62],{"class":48,"line":61},3,[46,63,64],{},"d8deea6aacf6: Preparing \n",[46,66,68],{"class":48,"line":67},4,[46,69,70],{},"d31b1b3688ec: Preparing \n",[46,72,74],{"class":48,"line":73},5,[46,75,76],{},"859d050b8423: Preparing \n",[46,78,80],{"class":48,"line":79},6,[46,81,82],{},"5f70bf18a086: Preparing \n",[46,84,86],{"class":48,"line":85},7,[46,87,88],{},"9164c306cc0a: Preparing \n",[46,90,92],{"class":48,"line":91},8,[46,93,94],{},"8396c878c66c: Waiting \n",[46,96,98],{"class":48,"line":97},9,[46,99,100],{},"3ee39e78fd25: Waiting \n",[46,102,104],{"class":48,"line":103},10,[46,105,106],{},"138331e9552c: Waiting \n",[46,108,110],{"class":48,"line":109},11,[46,111,112],{},"denied: requested access to the resource is denied\n",[17,114,115],{},[116,117],"img",{"alt":118,"src":119},"requested access to the resource is denied","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-04-23%2021.51.26.png",[12,121,123],{"id":122},"fixes-to-try","Fixes to try",[17,125,126],{},"Here's a rundown of what to check.",[17,128,129,130,133,134,137,138,141,142,145],{},"Quick context first: when you push to Docker Hub, the image name has to be ",[21,131,132],{},"username\u002FimageName",". So if your local image is ",[21,135,136],{},"test"," and your Docker Hub username is ",[21,139,140],{},"hsiangfeng",", you'd run ",[21,143,144],{},"docker push hsiangfeng\u002Ftest",".",[147,148,150],"h3",{"id":149},"check-login-status","Check login status",[17,152,153,154,157],{},"First, run ",[21,155,156],{},"docker login"," to make sure you're logged in.",[17,159,160],{},[116,161],{"alt":162,"src":163},"Login Succeeded","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-04-23%2021.53.12.png",[17,165,166],{},"If you were already logged in, try logging out and back in:",[37,168,172],{"className":169,"code":170,"language":171,"meta":42,"style":42},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","docker logout\n","bash",[21,173,174],{"__ignoreMap":42},[46,175,176,180],{"class":48,"line":49},[46,177,179],{"class":178},"s_sBn","docker",[46,181,183],{"class":182},"sTRMh"," logout\n",[17,185,186],{},[116,187],{"alt":188,"src":189},"logout","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-04-23%2021.55.08.png",[17,191,192,193,195,196,145],{},"Then ",[21,194,156],{}," again, and retry ",[21,197,34],{},[17,199,200],{},"A lot of people report this is enough to fix it.",[147,202,204],{"id":203},"forgot-to-update-tag-name","Forgot to update tag name",[17,206,207,208,210],{},"Sometimes you forgot to update the tag name. Docker uses tags to identify what you're pushing, so the remote Docker Hub account namespace has to match your local image name. If your local image is ",[21,209,136],{},", you need to tag it:",[37,212,214],{"className":39,"code":213,"language":41,"meta":42,"style":42},"docker tag test username\u002Ftest\n",[21,215,216],{"__ignoreMap":42},[46,217,218],{"class":48,"line":49},[46,219,213],{},[17,221,222,223,225,226,229,230,233,234,237],{},"For my Docker Hub account ",[21,224,140],{},", that'd be ",[21,227,228],{},"docker tag test hsiangfeng\u002Ftest",". Then run ",[21,231,232],{},"docker images"," and you should see the ",[21,235,236],{},"hsiangfeng\u002Ftest"," image.",[17,239,240],{},[116,241],{"alt":232,"src":242},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E8%B2%BC%E4%B8%8A%E7%9A%84%E5%BD%B1%E5%83%8F_2022_4_23_22_02.png",[17,244,245,246,248],{},"Try ",[21,247,144],{}," again.",[12,250,252],{"id":251},"forgot-to-create-the-repository","Forgot to create the Repository",[17,254,255,256,258],{},"One last one — kind of dumb. When you run ",[21,257,144],{},", Docker doesn't auto-create the repository for you. Head to Docker Hub and create the repository manually with the matching name.",[17,260,261],{},[116,262],{"alt":263,"src":264},"Create repository","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-04-23%2022.27.47.png",[17,266,267,268,270],{},"Then retry ",[21,269,144],{},". This usually does it.",[17,272,273],{},[116,274],{"alt":275,"src":276},"Success","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-04-23%2022.29.02.png",[12,278,280],{"id":279},"references","References",[282,283,284],"ul",{},[285,286,287],"li",{},[288,289,293],"a",{"href":290,"rel":291},"https:\u002F\u002Fstackoverflow.com\u002Fquestions\u002F43858398\u002Fdocker-push-error-denied-requested-access-to-the-resource-is-denied",[292],"nofollow","docker push error \"denied: requested access to the resource is denied\"",[295,296,297],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}",{"title":42,"searchDepth":55,"depth":55,"links":299},[300,301,302,306,307],{"id":14,"depth":55,"text":15},{"id":27,"depth":55,"text":28},{"id":122,"depth":55,"text":123,"children":303},[304,305],{"id":149,"depth":61,"text":150},{"id":203,"depth":61,"text":204},{"id":251,"depth":55,"text":252},{"id":279,"depth":55,"text":280},"Docker","2022-04-23 21:43:26","Tried to docker push to Docker Hub and kept hitting 'denied: requested access to the resource is denied'? All the fixes — image naming, login state, and tag format.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix","2",{"title":6,"description":310},false,"en\u002FDocker\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix",[308,321],"Troubleshooting",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F23\u002Fdocker-denied-requested-access-fix\u002F","H7yBAdyNNhxPSuZZgo2IgtEi0CZ4K8p12Gua-4MWm2s",{"newer":326,"older":330},{"url":327,"title":328,"date":329},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F28\u002Fdiscord-beginners-complete-guide\u002F","Discord Beginner's Guide: From Sign-Up to Daily Use (Complete Walkthrough)","2022-04-28 21:00:46",{"url":331,"title":332,"date":333},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fjs-core-76-promise-chaining\u002F","JavaScript Core (76) - Promise Chaining: How then and catch Actually Flow","2022-04-17 19:38:51",[335,339,344],{"url":336,"title":337,"date":338,"readingMinutes":316},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2024\u002F12\u002F19\u002Fdockerize-vite-vue-project\u002F","How to Dockerize a Vite + Vue Project","2024-12-19 16:36:18",{"url":340,"title":341,"date":342,"readingMinutes":343},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-table-of-contents\u002F","(11) Step-by-Step Docker — Table of Contents","2023-01-29 15:22:19","1",{"url":345,"title":346,"date":347,"readingMinutes":316},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F","(10) Step-by-Step Docker — Docker GUI","2023-01-29 15:20:19",1784013057226]